The paper deals with diversification of results in query processing, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a framework and implementation algorithms, which involve data structures and algorithms (DS) and machine learning (LG) techniques. Finally, the paper performs experiments on real and synthetic data, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and data analysis.
